{
  "stem": "10572.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the next day, I-- I went to our rabbi, who was a relatively new rabbi, young-- young rabbi, was a good friend of mine, Josef Schwartz, who later on ended up to be a rabbi in Benton Harbor, Michigan after going to Manila and being a prisoner of the Japanese.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And asked him to write a letter to Mrs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Hamilton as a reference, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because my father was skeptic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Told me, sure.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Said, she's coming back home to America.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she will tell her husband what she has done here.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and he will say to her, are you completely meshuggah?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Bring four people over here.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You are responsible for them?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I sat down, and I wrote a letter thanking her and-- and sending her a book about my-- about Hildesheim, which was magnificent.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was one of the most beautiful cities.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she knew it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so now I waited and waited.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was the 23rd of August, 1938.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the 23rd of September happened and nothing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't hear.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father, knowing [LAUGHS] the ways of the world, said, you know, forget about the whole thing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] There was an old saying.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] [NON-ENGLISH] is when you have second thoughts about something.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And said, she went back and-- so on the 6th of October, I got the letter-- the letter.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a long, long, letter.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you will find the letter in my story that I wrote in memory of Mrs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Hamilton.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The letter said that she came back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "At first she was busy with getting her daughters ready for school, to go back to school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- but she told her husband of this experience.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she wanted to tell us that her husband was in full accord with her promise.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And on her way home, she had stopped-- after they got to New York, she had gone to Columbus, Ohio and stopped at friends of theirs.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] she said this friend had a big department store in Columbus.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I didn't know Columbus, Ohio.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I didn't know Ohio.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I didn't know-- I didn't know America.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I didn't know what-- what she was talking about when she talked about Columbus, Ohio and that her friend had a big department store there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he said to her that if I would come here, and I couldn't find any other job, he would give me a job in his store.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I didn't know at that time that this friend was Herbert Lazarus of Lazarus Department Stores in Columbus, Ohio, who also owned Bloomingdale's and also owned Filene, and also owned Abraham and Straus, and so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And-- and Mrs.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Lazarus, Hettie Weiler God bless her soul, was Mrs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Hamilton's roommate, class of 1914 at Wellesley.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I'm convinced-- I'm still convinced today, even though Mrs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Hamilton's daughters have denied it, that it was this friendship-- this lifelong friendship, very, very close friendship with this Jewish girl-- [CRYING] That opened her heart.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "[CRYING] Now.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Come on.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And-- I said in the story, which I wrote many, many years later in memory of Mrs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Hamilton, she was a unbelievable human being.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And we were privileged to be her friend for 28 years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And she had the sensitivity and the-- she had respect for our sensitivities.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And she did things that were so unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that many, many, many years later, on our 50th-- 50th anniversary that I met Mrs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hamilton-- Margie and I had inherited some money from an aunt of Margie's, who was a very, very favorite aunt of mine, another remarkable woman.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we went to our lawyer and set up a fund [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] [CRYING] at Wellesley, [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] the Agusta Hamilton Fund for Jewish Studies [CRYING] at Wellesley.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
